Public transportation model using LLM/agent controlled city grid of autonomous vehicles 


Overview of the transportation system this app will simulate:
*************************************************************

H = human
S = Agent-controlling System, probably LLM
C = car
D = destination


H requests destination on phone app

S plots several routes from start to D

S checks all already-requested routes for intersection/conflict with other Cs on each plotted route to find the ideal with regard to time. Avoiding system gridlock as much as possible is the third goal behind 1) safety 2) use fastest route for that H

S dispatches C directly to D, H walks out the door, touches phone to window sensor to authenticate that is the correct H for this ride, C opens

H does phone, reads etc while C leaves for D starting on ideal route

C uses camera, lidar, proximity sensor to avoid collisions with any un-plotted, unexpected still or moving obstacles encountered along the route, like jaywalking pedestrians, vehicles driven by humans, animals, construction vehicles, which there should be few

C is fully aware of all other cars along the route, via S’s knowledge of them and their precise locations, but also through proximity and visual data Cs are collecting, which is also shared with S as feedback to maintain a known system state of the moving grid

If a H touches a certain button or uses a certain word inside the C, another human takes over the vehicle from a remote location immediately.  That human can fully control C and see all cameras and sensors and is fully trained to drive C

Human traffic police will be brought directly to another C in seconds if any alarms are sounded, and interior of Cs as well as pick up events are monitored (no forced entry into vehicle behind passenger on pickup possible without traffic police pulling up in seconds)

H is delivered to destination.  If H will be only a short time, the C may idle outside for return trip, if longer C may leave to shuttle another H in the meantime, then another C may appear when H is ready to return home.



Task
*****

Create a 2D mapped simulation of a simple, small metro area that demonstrates this public transportation model.  The metro area will have 4 main employers, 2 grocery stores, 2 schools, and a train station used as a drop-off point where people can transfer from individual cars to an automated train that demonstrates taking then to a different metro area out of this simulation.

There will be two types of cars: 4-passenger sedans and 8-passenger shuttle busses.  The 8-passenger vehicles are often used to pick up people who need to go to the same location at the same time, like a work or school schedule or to the train station.  4-passenger sedans are usually shuttling 1 or 2 people somewhere. 

The app will have two modes: just simulate a fully running metro area, with people calling cars, cars delivering to destination, speeded up simulation, very busy but following all the rules.  2nd mode is interactive, with the user entering a source and destination and having the app walk through the major decision it would make to plot the route, and then simulate a step by step run of the route displaying how the car would avoid unexpected obstacles using camera/lidar/proximity and know about other cars.

The app should display an attractive and responsive ‘city’ with street grid, vehicles, etc.
   
